<p>The onesie is for a baby aged 3-6 months, which my baby was once. It no longer fits him because he is, as I keep telling him, <em>such a big boy now yes he is</em>. The fabric was from Cloth House, the body is called <a href="https://www.clothhouse.com/cotton-prints-stripes-checks/japanese-wind">â€œJapanese Wind Whiteâ€</a>, and the binding is <a href="https://www.clothhouse.com/cotton-prints-stripes-checks/japanese-wind-navy">â€œJapanese Wind Navyâ€</a>. Those links donâ€™t work at the moment because the website is â€œclosed for Christmasâ€ (lol ok).</p>

<p>This was really fun to sew and my son looked extremely cute in it. This onesie works well in summer but looks a bit strange under trousers because it is so puffy around the tum.</p>

